# Identity federation

Let **external identities assume roles** — no IAM user, no long-lived password.

## Two protocols

- **SAML 2.0** — enterprise IdPs (ADFS, Okta) → `AssumeRoleWithSAML`
- **OIDC** — Google, EKS, GitHub Actions → `AssumeRoleWithWebIdentity`

## IAM Identity Center — the modern way

- Lives in the **management account**; one source of truth (AD, Okta, Entra ID)
- **One sign-on portal** → every account + role; calls `AssumeRole` for you

## Permission set — its unit

A template of policies (+ optional boundary / session length). Define once → provisions a hidden role per account; update once → everywhere.

**Default to Identity Center over per-account IAM users.**
